Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: frankly-fw-update-cli
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: CLI tool for updating firmware on Frankly Bootloader devices
 This package provides a command-line interface for updating firmware
 on embedded devices using the Frankly Bootloader protocol. It supports
 multiple communication interfaces including Serial, CAN, Ethernet, and
 simulated devices.
 .
 Features include:
  - Device discovery and scanning
  - Application erasing
  - Firmware flashing from Intel HEX files
  - Device reset
  - Support for Serial, CAN, Ethernet, and SIM interfaces

Package: frankly-fw-update-tui
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Terminal UI for updating firmware on Frankly Bootloader devices
 This package provides an interactive terminal user interface for updating
 firmware on embedded devices using the Frankly Bootloader protocol.
 .
 The TUI provides a menu-driven experience with features including:
  - Interactive device discovery
  - Guided operation selection (Search, Erase, Flash, Reset)
  - File browser for selecting firmware files
  - Live progress display during operations
  - Support for Serial, CAN, Ethernet, and SIM interfaces
